svg.desc: The chart shows the proportion of persons with at least secondary school (II) graduation by age group and migration background in 2016. Some 92 percent of people without a migration background have at least one secondary school (II) graduation, for people with a migration background the figure is some 68 percent. The proportion of migrants with a secondary school (II) graduation increases in younger age brackets. For example, 74 percent of people with a migration background aged 25-34 have at least one secondary school (II) graduation. In the 55-64 age group, the figure was 63.8 percent.

div.p:
Source: German Federal Statistical Office, Results of the 2016 Microcensus.
